memberOrga:
TAFISA members are classified into three categories:&#xd;
1. National members: state or non-state institutions operating at the national level that actively promote general Sport for All and physical activity and have the promotion of Sport for All and physical activity included in their legally binding statutes or equivalent documents.&#xd;
2. International members: institutions that actively promote Sport for All and physical activity internationally, and have the promotion of Sport for All and physical activity included in their legal binding statutes or equivalent document.&#xd;
3. Supporting members: individuals or organisations, including national specific sports organisations, provincial organisations, academic institutions or commercial institutions, as well as public or private institutions, including city or community administrations, offering or actively promoting Sport for All and physical activity.&#xd;
